  "market_context": "Bullish daily bias on NQ1! through late May into early June 2025. Analyst walks the hourly chart forward bar-by-bar, identifying expansion–consolidation–reversal sequences and pairing them with daily candle closures to filter intraday continuation versus reversal setups.",
  "key_observation": "Expansion met with opposing expansion forms a higher time frame wick and signals a reversal; pairing this with daily closures, protected swings, and change in state of delivery filters out unclean moves and isolates the easier continuation trades aligned with daily bias.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Establish that hourly chart is used together with daily closures and daily bias, with bullish bias requiring a manipulation of lows or a breakout-retracement continuation higher.",
    "Step 2: Identify first sequence — expansion into consolidation around 21,640–21,720; wait for either a retracement (protected swing entry), consolidation low sweep, or reversal.",
    "Step 3: Observe that price takes out the consolidation low but fails to close over down-close candles, so no continuation signature forms; stay bullish since daily bias has not changed.",
    "Step 4: Note expansion lower met with expansion higher off the low — defines a reversal — then anticipate continuation higher into the new day, which prints.",
    "Step 5: Next sequence — expansion into consolidation again; price expands through the high but immediately gets met with opposing expansion, signalling another reversal targeting the consolidation low.",
    "Step 6: Price fails to push higher, breaks down, runs the prior low with expansion–retracement–expansion lower into late New York, confirming the reversal scenario.",
    "Step 7: After failed manipulation of the higher consolidation low, look for expansion vs. expansion at the swing; once the daily candle closes back inside the range, combine daily closure + CISD + expansion-met-with-expansion → all three confirm reversal higher.",
    "Step 8: Anticipate continuation up via retracement or consolidation-then-sweep; price delivers a slow shallow retracement paired with intraday CISD → valid long entry aligned with bias.",
    "Step 9: After continuation expansion, set target as the prior relevant high (reversals occur at relevant highs/lows), not an arbitrary level.",
    "Step 10: At the next test of resistance near 22,075/21,925, price consolidates and never sweeps a low for re-entry, so the move is skipped — system filter prevents chasing unclean continuation.",
    "Step 11: Final sequence sweeps a high with CISD on the hourly suggesting reversal, but the analyst waits for daily candle closure confirmation before flipping bias, mirroring the earlier successful long setup."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long continuation entries triggered by the failed manipulation + daily closure + CISD sequence played out higher; the later consolidation move was filtered out by the system because no protected swing or low-sweep formed. No specific R:R or fill price stated.",
  "lessons": "Blending phases of price with daily candle closures, protected swings, and change in state of delivery filters noise: take continuation entries only when daily bias, phase transition, and CISD align, and skip unclean moves rather than forcing trades.",
